            ; and</p>
               <p>Eight other counts for like offence, only varying the manner of charging them.</p>
               <p>The indictment was read by Mr. Reynolds, and the case stated by Mr. Knapp.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18080914-121-person1082">
                  REUBEN 
                  FLETCHER
               <interp inst="t18080914-121-person1082" type="surname" value="FLETCHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18080914-121-person1082" type="given" value="REUBEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18080914-121-person1082" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . - Mr. Reynolds. Are you one of the <rs id="t18080914-121-viclabel703" type="occupation">moniers of the mint</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18080914-121-victim1073 t18080914-121-viclabel703"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18080914-121-victim1075 t18080914-121-viclabel703"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18080914-121-victim1077 t18080914-121-viclabel703"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18080914-121-victim1079 t18080914-121-viclabel703"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18080914-121-victim1081 t18080914-121-viclabel703"></join> - A. I am.</p>
               <p>Q. Who are the moniers - A. 
               <persName id="t18080914-121-person1083">
                  Joseph 
                  Sage
               <interp inst="t18080914-121-person1083" type="surname" value="Sage"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18080914-121-person1083" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
